WEBVTT

00:15.240 --> 00:16.240
Please, God...

00:17.720 --> 00:18.720
Not this time.

00:34.240 --> 00:37.640
♪ Broken windows and empty hallways

00:38.600 --> 00:43.080
♪ A pale, dead moon in the sky
streaked with grey

00:45.080 --> 00:48.920
♪ Human kindness is overflowing

00:49.800 --> 00:56.080
♪ And I think it's going to rain today ♪

01:29.000 --> 01:32.160
In the name of the Father,
and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit.

01:34.640 --> 01:37.400
Grace of our Lord Jesus Christ
and the love of God

01:38.160 --> 01:40.600
and the communion of
the Holy Spirit be with you all.

01:41.120 --> 01:43.120
We have some...
We have some guests here today.

01:43.400 --> 01:47.760
Parents with children who are making
their first holy communion next week,

01:47.840 --> 01:51.080
so I'm just gonna stop
and explain things at times.

01:51.240 --> 01:55.680
That might make the mass a little longer
but hopefully more enjoyable.

01:56.800 --> 01:59.840
Brothers and sisters,
let us acknowledge our sins.

02:00.040 --> 02:03.600
And so prepare ourselves to celebrate
the sacred mistress.

02:04.960 --> 02:06.840
I confess to Almighty God...

02:08.000 --> 02:10.040
ALL: And to you,
my brothers and sisters,

02:10.760 --> 02:12.560
that I have greatly sinned.

02:12.960 --> 02:14.880
MICHAEL: And it's now that
God changes the bread

02:14.960 --> 02:16.360
into the body of Christ

02:16.720 --> 02:18.440
and the wine into his blood.

02:18.760 --> 02:20.280
There's gonna be a bell
that will ring here,

02:20.360 --> 02:23.280
and that dates back from old days,
where everything was in Latin

02:23.360 --> 02:27.560
and no one knew what was going on,
so the bell meant this bit's important.

02:27.760 --> 02:28.800
-[BELL RINGS]
-[CHUCKLES]

02:31.760 --> 02:33.320
For, on the night He was betrayed,

02:35.080 --> 02:37.400
He himself took bread

02:37.880 --> 02:40.560
and, giving you thanks,
He said the blessing,

02:41.320 --> 02:42.320
broke the bread,

02:43.200 --> 02:45.200
and gave it to his disciples saying,

02:45.600 --> 02:47.560
"Take this, all of you,

02:47.920 --> 02:49.200
"and eat of it.

02:49.880 --> 02:52.840
"For this is my body which
will be given up for you."

02:53.320 --> 02:54.320
[BELL RINGS]

02:56.680 --> 02:59.080
In the similar way,
when supper was ended,

02:59.640 --> 03:00.760
He took the chalice,

03:02.000 --> 03:04.720
and, giving you thanks,
He said the blessing

03:05.360 --> 03:08.000
and gave the chalice
to his disciples saying,

03:08.440 --> 03:10.720
"Take this, all of you,

03:11.720 --> 03:12.720
"and drink of it.

03:14.520 --> 03:16.440
"For this is the chalice of my blood."

03:16.600 --> 03:19.800
You dirty, filthy beast! You horror!

03:20.280 --> 03:21.280
The blood...

03:21.920 --> 03:22.960
WOMAN: Have you got no shame?

03:23.680 --> 03:24.680
"The blood..."

03:24.760 --> 03:26.920
Have you got no bloody shame!

03:27.000 --> 03:30.720
"Of the new and the eternal covenant

03:30.800 --> 03:32.440
"which will be poured out for you."

03:32.520 --> 03:34.840
You dirty, filthy beast!

03:36.120 --> 03:40.120
"Do this in memory of me."

03:40.800 --> 03:41.800
[BELL RINGS]

04:01.840 --> 04:03.840
MICHAEL: No, that's all gone, thank God.

04:03.960 --> 04:05.560
I mean, the idea of a child

04:05.640 --> 04:07.320
-of nine having anything to confess...
-[MOBILE RINGING]

04:07.400 --> 04:10.840
Let alone a list of things.
Well, I find that a bit...

04:11.040 --> 04:12.280
-I find that a bit harsh...
-[RINGING CONTINUES]

04:12.600 --> 04:13.600
Um...

04:14.000 --> 04:16.920
Now, what we do now
is a general absolution

04:17.200 --> 04:19.800
at the start of the mass, and that
includes everyone, of course.

04:19.880 --> 04:22.560
-Not just the children, everyone...
-[MOBILE RINGING]

04:23.120 --> 04:24.920
The children, everyone.

04:25.200 --> 04:26.480
-I'm sorry.
-It's all right.

04:26.560 --> 04:28.280
-Obviously got a lot on your plate.
-Yeah, I have.

04:29.760 --> 04:32.200
I'm sorry, I'm not playing
the naughty little school girl saying

04:32.280 --> 04:34.040
I have got a lot on my plate.
I was, um...

04:35.200 --> 04:37.600
I wasn't expecting this.
I wasn't expecting an hour-long mass

04:37.680 --> 04:39.640
before the meeting.
So, I'm really sorry, darling.

04:39.720 --> 04:41.720
-I run a shop, I'm...
-MICHAEL: Yeah.

04:41.800 --> 04:43.080
I'm 40 minutes late, I wasn't there,

04:43.160 --> 04:45.560
the boss is now gonna open it up
and I'm gonna be in the shit!

04:45.680 --> 04:46.760
MICHAEL: Well, uh...

04:46.920 --> 04:49.640
-I'm sorry, I'm not swearing...
-Is, uh, is your mum at home?

04:49.720 --> 04:50.720
-What?
-[MOBILE RINGS]

04:50.800 --> 04:53.760
It your mum in now? You could get off
and we could drop Lisa.

04:53.880 --> 04:55.840
-It's Lisa. Is it Lisa?
-Yeah. Yeah.

04:56.120 --> 04:57.240
Yeah, we could drop Lisa.

04:57.320 --> 04:58.680
-I've come with Ms Pickering and...
-Yeah?

04:59.040 --> 05:00.840
-Are you gonna be all right?
-Yeah.

05:01.000 --> 05:02.960
I'm sorry, love. I'm really sorry.

05:03.720 --> 05:05.960
-All right, don't worry. See you.
-I'm really, really sorry!

05:07.280 --> 05:08.320
Okay.

05:09.560 --> 05:12.520
It's Christina Fitzsimmons here, Jean,
I'm returning your call.

05:12.840 --> 05:13.840
Um...

05:13.960 --> 05:15.800
I couldn't talk in church,
it's a long story.

05:15.880 --> 05:19.040
I'll explain when I get there, I should
be about 10 minutes, all right?

05:19.560 --> 05:21.040
Thanks. Bye.

05:33.560 --> 05:35.840
I'm sorry, Jean.
I'm really, really sorry!

05:35.920 --> 05:38.960
Our Lisa's taking the first
communion next week.

05:39.280 --> 05:41.600
I know you don't like hearing
about other people's kids, but anyway.

05:42.440 --> 05:43.720
[SIGHS] Oh, the meeting

05:44.320 --> 05:46.320
was supposed to be at 9:00 a.m.,
but what they didn't tell me

05:46.680 --> 05:49.320
is there was gonna be an hour-long
mass before that even started.

05:50.080 --> 05:52.760
-I'm so, so sorry I'm late.
-What's that?

05:57.880 --> 05:59.520
-It's an IOU.
-60 quid?

05:59.600 --> 06:00.640
Yeah.

06:00.920 --> 06:03.080
But what's a 60 quid IOU
doing in one of our tills?

06:03.160 --> 06:05.680
-I borrowed 60 quid.
-No, no, no, you took 60 quid.

06:05.760 --> 06:07.600
-No, I did not...
-You stole 60 quid.

06:07.680 --> 06:08.680
-I didn't...
-You're a thief.

06:08.760 --> 06:11.040
I'm not a thief, Jean.
Because a thief doesn't leave

06:11.120 --> 06:13.480
an IOU note saying that
I owe you 60 quid, does he?

06:13.560 --> 06:15.120
-Would you take 10 grand then?
-No!

06:15.360 --> 06:17.200
You wouldn't take 10 grand
and sign a note saying,

06:17.280 --> 06:19.080
"I owe you 10 grand,"
that'd be theft, yeah?

06:19.160 --> 06:21.000
-Yeah, of course it would...
-Then why isn't that theft?

06:21.120 --> 06:24.160
Because, Jean, it's 60 quid,
and I can pay back 60 quid.

06:24.240 --> 06:26.080
I couldn't pay back 10 grand, could I?

06:26.680 --> 06:28.160
-Show me, then.
-Show you what?

06:28.520 --> 06:30.560
-Show me the 60 quid.
-I haven't got 60 quid.

06:30.680 --> 06:31.840
Then when were you thinking
of paying it back?

06:31.920 --> 06:33.560
Pay day. I'm sorry,
if you've heard this before,

06:33.640 --> 06:35.360
but I've got three kids to feed, Jean.

06:35.440 --> 06:38.040
And the shitty money that you pay,
a pound an hour above

06:38.120 --> 06:40.920
the minimum wage, won't cover that,
which is why I took 60 quid.

06:41.040 --> 06:43.080
In fact, I didn't take 60 quid,
I borrowed 60 quid.

06:43.160 --> 06:44.440
-You're sacked.
-What?

06:44.560 --> 06:48.080
You heard me, you're sacked.
Now, piss off before I phone the police.

06:48.160 --> 06:50.240
You just said yourself
it's shitty money,

06:50.320 --> 06:52.480
so sod off and find summat better.

06:58.680 --> 06:59.920
Right, well, you owe me, um...

07:01.000 --> 07:02.000
You owe me two weeks...

07:02.560 --> 07:04.400
-Two weeks wages.
-Oh, you'll get them in due course.

07:04.480 --> 07:05.640
No, I need it now, I'm skint.

07:05.720 --> 07:07.800
Oh, you're half way through the month
and you're skint already?

07:07.880 --> 07:09.440
-Yeah, I am.
-And what were you gonna do?

07:09.640 --> 07:11.280
-Take even more out of my till?
-Yeah, I was,

07:11.360 --> 07:12.600
because half the staff are doing it,

07:12.680 --> 07:14.080
they're all borrowing money
from the till

07:14.160 --> 07:15.640
because the money you pay is shite.

07:15.720 --> 07:18.080
Well, then, at the risk
of repeating myself,

07:18.160 --> 07:20.120
you sod off and find summat better.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.080
You and your three bleeding kids.

07:22.160 --> 07:23.160
You...

07:23.920 --> 07:24.920
[GRUNTS]

07:26.280 --> 07:27.280
Get off me!

07:28.160 --> 07:29.160
[VIDEO GAME MUSIC PLAYS]

07:29.240 --> 07:31.360
-[BOTH GRUNTING]
-CHRISTINA: Get off me!

07:50.400 --> 07:51.400
[INAUDIBLE CHATTERING]

07:52.040 --> 07:54.000
WOMAN: What are you doing here?

07:54.600 --> 07:58.000
Oh, love, I'm sorry, I forgot that
he was bringing you home.

07:58.080 --> 08:00.320
-What's happened?
-Lisa, no... Lis!

08:01.400 --> 08:02.400
Lisa!

08:04.080 --> 08:05.080
I've, um...

08:05.560 --> 08:08.440
I had a barney with the area manager
after she sacked me.

08:08.520 --> 08:10.000
-Sacked you?
-What, for being late?

08:10.280 --> 08:12.640
Yeah. Well, no, not quite, really.

08:12.840 --> 08:14.480
If I hadn't been late,
she wouldn't have opened up

08:14.560 --> 08:16.360
and found an IOU for 60 quid.

08:16.440 --> 08:19.120
So, yeah, basically, for being late.

08:19.440 --> 08:20.840
-I'm sorry.
-Thanks.

08:22.240 --> 08:24.040
Why do people go to mass, Father?

08:24.480 --> 08:27.360
-Oh, lots of reasons.
-But they get something out of it, yeah?

08:27.600 --> 08:29.720
-Yeah.
-Well, I got this and this

08:30.200 --> 08:33.960
and I got the sack. If I go tomorrow
what am I gonna get, cystitis?

08:39.000 --> 08:40.000
MICHAEL: See you, boys.

08:45.280 --> 08:46.440
If there's anything I can do...

08:46.560 --> 08:48.880
-[KNOCKS ON DOOR]
-[SIGHS] Oh, come on, Lisa.

08:51.400 --> 08:52.400
All right, I'll let you get on.

08:54.000 --> 08:55.000
Thanks, Father.

08:55.240 --> 08:57.120
Lisa, will you move away from the door?

08:57.240 --> 08:58.520
I'm gonna come in
and I don't wanna hurt you,

08:58.600 --> 09:01.200
so just move away
from the door, please. Lisa...

09:17.920 --> 09:18.920
You see this?

09:21.200 --> 09:24.040
That's all gonna be gone
by the time it's your communion.

09:26.200 --> 09:27.640
It'll all be gone.

09:29.280 --> 09:30.800
Look at me.

09:30.920 --> 09:32.960
I'll be all gorgeous again.

09:36.720 --> 09:38.280
Come here.

09:38.880 --> 09:40.200
You know that...

09:40.640 --> 09:43.280
You know that lovely dress that
you wanted, the one with the veil?

09:43.960 --> 09:45.400
I'm gonna get you that.

09:48.520 --> 09:49.760
It's too much.

09:50.120 --> 09:51.560
No, it's not.

09:52.800 --> 09:54.600
It's not, I'm gonna get it for you.

09:55.640 --> 09:58.240
[SIGHS] Nothing's too
much for you, is it?

10:01.800 --> 10:04.960
MAN: I'm going to read
you a poem about a hawk.

10:05.560 --> 10:07.840
You will take it home
and you'll write about it.

10:08.200 --> 10:10.200
Whoever writes the best composition

10:10.480 --> 10:11.480
wins this,

10:11.680 --> 10:13.760
which is also about a hawk.

10:16.400 --> 10:19.600
"I caught this morning,
morning's minion,

10:19.960 --> 10:22.520
"kingdom of daylight's dauphin.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.560
"Dapple-dawn-drawn falcon,

10:25.800 --> 10:29.800
"in his riding of the rolling level
underneath him, steady air

10:30.520 --> 10:32.720
"and striding high there.

10:33.600 --> 10:36.400
"How he rung upon the rein
of a wimpling wing

10:36.600 --> 10:38.000
"in his ecstasy.

10:38.480 --> 10:39.480
"Then, off.

10:40.360 --> 10:42.280
"Off forth on swing,

10:42.600 --> 10:45.800
"as a skate's heel sweeps smooth

10:46.040 --> 10:47.080
"on a bow-bend.

10:47.160 --> 10:50.640
"My heart in hiding stirred

10:51.080 --> 10:53.360
"for a bird, the achieve of,

10:54.200 --> 10:56.040
"the mastery of the thing.

10:56.520 --> 10:58.840
"And the fire that breaks
from thee, then

10:58.960 --> 11:01.520
"a billion times told lovelier,

11:01.600 --> 11:05.240
"more dangerous, O my chevalier."

11:05.920 --> 11:08.400
YOUNG MICHAEL: "I like hawk.
I caught this morning.

11:08.480 --> 11:10.560
"It's as if you've caught hold of
a dove lark.

11:10.640 --> 11:13.520
"And it's taking us with it,
swooping and soaring.

11:14.200 --> 11:17.160
"And the M's are good too.
Morning, mornings, minion.

11:17.360 --> 11:19.400
"Because M is a shape of a bird.

11:20.080 --> 11:23.000
"And awning, awnings,
and then you're trailing after it.

11:23.440 --> 11:25.120
"And that could be us hanging on.

11:25.200 --> 11:26.200
[BANGS]

11:28.800 --> 11:31.320
"And then it drops so fast,
you can't slow it down.

11:33.360 --> 11:35.680
"Because it's quicker than down,
so has to be done.

11:36.480 --> 11:39.400
"And you can't pick words
beginning with Ds, it takes effort,

11:39.480 --> 11:41.960
"noisy effort the hawk is making
to climb back up there."

11:46.840 --> 11:47.840
Father...

11:48.680 --> 11:49.760
Who helped you?

11:51.560 --> 11:52.560
[SMACK]

11:56.160 --> 11:57.160
[SMACK]

11:59.640 --> 12:00.640
[SMACK]

12:03.640 --> 12:04.640
[SMACK]

12:06.920 --> 12:08.320
[SMACK]

12:10.280 --> 12:11.800
YOUNG MICHAEL: It's not fair.

12:13.280 --> 12:15.160
[INDISTINCT VOICE OVER SPEAKER]

12:23.640 --> 12:25.280
-So, we do it, yeah?
-Yeah.

12:25.920 --> 12:27.120
We draw up a roster.

12:27.520 --> 12:29.680
Beth will still do her two nights,
I'll do my one.

12:29.920 --> 12:31.960
That leaves four nights between
the seven of you.

12:32.480 --> 12:33.880
-Phil won't do one.
-He will.

12:34.560 --> 12:36.640
He didn't know Mum was dying,
but he knows now and he will.

12:36.720 --> 12:38.680
Just when you need a miracle,
it happens.

12:38.840 --> 12:40.640
Works out to just over once a fortnight.

12:40.720 --> 12:41.920
That's nothing.

12:42.440 --> 12:44.360
-You were second...
-Second, third, fourth,

12:44.440 --> 12:45.720
there's nothing in it, you prick.

12:45.800 --> 12:47.600
How can you go for me
when it's your lead?

12:47.680 --> 12:49.960
Didn't stop you going for me
two hands ago,

12:50.240 --> 12:51.560
you devious little shit.

12:51.640 --> 12:53.120
It was your blind two hands ago!

12:53.720 --> 12:57.120
You were practically level
two hands ago, you crying git.

12:57.200 --> 13:00.600
I was not practically level!
I was 62 behind.

13:00.680 --> 13:02.120
So, who's gonna do it?

13:04.400 --> 13:06.520
-What's up with you?
-She's dying!

13:07.640 --> 13:09.360
She can't be left alone overnight.

13:09.560 --> 13:12.520
Beth and Miss can't do it all on their
own, so we'll have to do our bit, yeah?

13:13.360 --> 13:15.800
Yeah, all right, so who's
gonna organise that?

13:16.800 --> 13:19.240
-You!
-Oh, no. Not me.

13:19.560 --> 13:21.520
62, 62...

13:21.680 --> 13:24.440
Yep. I bloody told you.

13:24.600 --> 13:25.760
All right, I'm going.

13:26.960 --> 13:27.960
What about us?

13:28.200 --> 13:29.800
I don't know, you have to have a 300
or summat.

13:29.880 --> 13:32.240
-[GROANS] Bloody hell.
-300 is shite.

13:32.880 --> 13:34.440
I'm sorry about that.

13:53.320 --> 13:54.320
-Hey!
-Hi.

13:54.680 --> 13:55.680
How are ya?

13:56.440 --> 13:58.000
-How's she been?
-Not bad.

13:58.160 --> 13:59.280
Michael's here, Mum.

13:59.920 --> 14:00.920
WOMAN: Hiya, son.

14:01.320 --> 14:02.320
Hiya, Mum.

14:02.560 --> 14:03.560
I'll be up in a minute.

14:05.000 --> 14:07.040
-She made me do her hair for you.
-Oh.

14:07.600 --> 14:09.800
-Tell her it looks nice.
-I will.

14:10.560 --> 14:12.120
-Bye, Mum.
-Bye, love.

14:12.720 --> 14:14.120
-Bye.
-Bye.

14:14.520 --> 14:15.920
-I'll see you later.
-See you later.

14:16.160 --> 14:17.160
Yeah.

14:24.040 --> 14:26.120
-How are you, Mum?
-How are you, son?

14:26.600 --> 14:27.600
MICHAEL: I'm great.

14:28.760 --> 14:29.760
You?

14:31.920 --> 14:33.240
I'm great, too.

14:34.280 --> 14:35.760
Your hair looks nice.

14:36.560 --> 14:37.560
Beth did it.

14:38.480 --> 14:39.880
It's lovely.

14:44.360 --> 14:50.360
ELLA FITZGERALD:
♪ Stars shining bright above you

14:50.720 --> 14:56.800
♪ Night breezes seem to whisper
I love you

14:57.440 --> 15:02.360
♪ Birds singing in the sycamore tree

15:03.240 --> 15:07.360
♪ Dream a little dream of me

15:09.840 --> 15:15.800
♪ Say nighty-night and kiss me

15:16.760 --> 15:22.120
♪ Just hold me tight
and tell me you'll miss me

15:23.200 --> 15:28.440
♪ While I'm alone and blue as can be

15:29.080 --> 15:34.520
♪ Dream a little dream of me

15:36.000 --> 15:40.640
LOUIS ARMSTRONG:
♪ Stars fading but I linger on, dear

15:40.720 --> 15:42.960
ELLA: ♪ Oh, how you linger on

15:43.320 --> 15:45.800
LOUIS: ♪ Still craving your kiss

15:45.920 --> 15:48.480
ELLA: ♪ How you crave my kiss

15:48.840 --> 15:54.120
LOUIS: ♪ Now I'm longing
to linger till dawn, dear

15:55.240 --> 15:58.640
♪ Just saying this

15:58.720 --> 16:00.960
ELLA: ♪ Give me a little kiss

16:01.240 --> 16:07.400
♪ Sweet dreams till sunbeams find you

16:07.560 --> 16:12.040
♪ Sweet dreams that leave
all worries behind you ♪

16:16.880 --> 16:19.920
-Right, how many 12s are in 60?
-I'm not having it.

16:20.000 --> 16:21.640
-Yes, you are.
-It's black.

16:21.800 --> 16:23.400
-[TV BLARING]
-It's fine. Oh, my God.

16:23.480 --> 16:25.440
-Can you turn that down?
-Five!

16:25.800 --> 16:27.600
-Five's right.
-I'll just have some porridge.

16:27.680 --> 16:30.480
No, you're gonna have that.
Will you turn that down?

16:30.760 --> 16:32.440
Five miles at 30 miles an hour.

16:32.640 --> 16:36.560
-Right. Mum, have you got any money?
-Uh, 15 quid and some coppers?

16:37.480 --> 16:40.120
You're gonna have to say that you
forgotten your dinner money, right?

16:40.640 --> 16:41.640
-Eat it.
-Can't he say it?

16:41.720 --> 16:42.840
No, he can't say it.

16:42.920 --> 16:44.640
-Five into 30?
-Six.

16:44.760 --> 16:48.120
-That's right. And then six into 60?
-Ten.

16:49.360 --> 16:50.360
Simple!

16:51.480 --> 16:53.840
-Will you lend us it?
-Of course.

16:54.120 --> 16:55.760
-Will you give me a letter?
-Saying what,

16:55.840 --> 16:57.880
that you forgot your dinner money
but you've remembered to bring

16:57.960 --> 17:01.080
a letter saying that you've forgotten
it? I think they might somehow...

17:01.160 --> 17:02.160
Ow!

17:07.800 --> 17:09.640
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

17:27.040 --> 17:28.360
Mrs Fitzsimmons.

17:36.560 --> 17:37.560
CLAIRE: Hi.

17:37.640 --> 17:39.920
WOMAN: We've got your form up
on screen, Mrs Fitzsimmons.

17:40.120 --> 17:41.160
CLAIRE: Right.

17:41.320 --> 17:43.000
Have you claimed job-seeker's
allowance before?

17:43.080 --> 17:46.800
No, I've worked since I left school.
Crap jobs, but I've always worked.

17:47.120 --> 17:49.640
And you know it's not for me to decide
on the merits of your claim?

17:50.040 --> 17:51.680
-Yeah, they explained that.
-Good.

17:51.960 --> 17:54.240
Nevertheless, you've put
down here you resigned?

17:54.680 --> 17:55.680
Yeah.

17:55.760 --> 17:56.760
Well, that's making
yourself intentionally

17:56.840 --> 17:58.360
unemployed, Mrs Fitzsimmons,

17:58.440 --> 18:00.800
which usually means
you can't claim for 13 weeks.

18:00.880 --> 18:02.800
-13 weeks?
-Yeah.

18:03.080 --> 18:04.080
I was sacked.

18:05.040 --> 18:06.600
-You were sacked?
-Yeah.

18:07.560 --> 18:09.040
Then why did you put you resigned?

18:10.760 --> 18:11.760
Um...

18:12.840 --> 18:15.800
'Cause I was ashamed of being sacked.

18:16.200 --> 18:17.200
Why were you sacked?

18:17.600 --> 18:18.760
Just a misunderstanding.

18:19.280 --> 18:21.760
We do check with
the employer, Mrs Fitzsimmons.

18:23.040 --> 18:27.480
I borrowed some money out of the till.
She'll say that it was theft,

18:27.680 --> 18:30.320
the area manager, but it wasn't,
I was gonna put it back.

18:30.640 --> 18:31.640
I see.

18:32.320 --> 18:33.920
-Anything else?
-Yeah, I punched her.

18:36.320 --> 18:38.000
That's not why I was sacked 'cause...

18:38.720 --> 18:41.520
Technically, I was already sacked,

18:41.920 --> 18:43.320
-when I punched her.
-I see.

18:44.680 --> 18:46.360
That's, um,

18:46.680 --> 18:48.160
as bad as resigning, yeah?

18:49.360 --> 18:51.360
People might think it worse,
Mrs Fitzsimmons,

18:51.760 --> 18:53.960
but the penalty might well
be the same. 13 weeks.

18:54.520 --> 18:56.240
But we'll notify you of that by letter.

18:59.560 --> 19:01.000
I've got three kids.

19:01.280 --> 19:03.720
-I'm sorry.
-There must be something I can claim.

19:03.840 --> 19:05.800
Social security, something?

19:05.880 --> 19:06.880
I'm afraid not.

19:07.520 --> 19:09.160
Is there a Mr Fitzsimmons?

19:09.480 --> 19:12.480
Yeah, but he hasn't given a penny since
the day I threw him out.

19:12.560 --> 19:14.400
-Well, maybe you should...
-No, there's no chance of that.

19:14.680 --> 19:16.480
Do you know anyone else who could
lend you some money?

19:16.880 --> 19:19.520
-Bono, McCartney, Elton John...
-Personally?

19:19.840 --> 19:23.000
-I mean, brother, sister...
-I don't know anyone who isn't skint.

19:24.560 --> 19:26.520
I've got three kids and no money.

19:26.960 --> 19:29.560
There must be something
I can claim to feed my kids.

19:29.640 --> 19:31.400
There might be the possibility of
of an emergency loan,

19:31.480 --> 19:33.720
but we'd consider that only
when you've made genuine attempts

19:33.800 --> 19:35.160
to borrow the money yourself.

19:35.240 --> 19:38.120
All right, and who decides
what's genuine?

19:38.200 --> 19:40.760
Well, obviously, a successful attempt
must've been genuine.

19:42.120 --> 19:45.160
But I wouldn't need the money
then, would I?

19:46.080 --> 19:47.920
No.

20:00.560 --> 20:02.040
-Sorry I'm late.
-It's okay.

20:03.400 --> 20:05.280
Next is the first holy communion.

20:05.560 --> 20:08.880
Nothing but praise for last year's,
Pauline, thanks very much.

20:08.960 --> 20:10.880
So, if you're prepared
to take it on again?

20:11.080 --> 20:12.080
Yeah. Yeah.

20:12.360 --> 20:14.560
In that case, same again
this time, yes?

20:14.640 --> 20:17.320
-Yeah. Just... Just one thing.
-Yes, Father?

20:17.440 --> 20:20.480
Um, it's just the cost with that.

20:20.720 --> 20:21.720
The cost?

20:22.360 --> 20:24.600
Yes. I know last year,

20:24.720 --> 20:28.000
um, a few families go
into debt with everything.

20:28.160 --> 20:30.760
You know, the dress, the party,
all the bits and pieces and that...

20:31.720 --> 20:34.400
I just think this year
there'll be more doing it.

20:34.600 --> 20:37.360
Well, the ceremony itself
costs nothing, Father.

20:37.440 --> 20:39.240
We ask them every year
to keep it simple,

20:39.320 --> 20:41.280
and they just get more and more...

20:43.360 --> 20:44.360
-Vulgar.
-Mmm-hmm.

20:45.520 --> 20:48.360
But there's one thing
we could ask them to do.

20:49.280 --> 20:50.280
Yeah?

20:50.680 --> 20:52.880
We could ask them to do
it in their school uniform.

20:53.960 --> 20:56.000
No suits, no fancy frocks.

20:57.440 --> 20:58.440
Pauline?

21:02.640 --> 21:03.840
Would people want that?

21:05.120 --> 21:06.160
Yeah, perhaps.

21:06.560 --> 21:09.880
But it would look like an ordinary mass.
There'll be nothing

21:10.240 --> 21:12.280
you could do to make
it any different from...

21:12.800 --> 21:13.800
Well...

21:14.040 --> 21:17.960
Father, you say fancy frocks,
but they're not just fancy,

21:18.040 --> 21:19.560
are they? They're white.

21:20.480 --> 21:23.040
-They're symbols of purity...
-Oh, they're 8 years old.

21:23.960 --> 21:25.560
Dress them in rags,
they'd still be pure.

21:27.480 --> 21:31.720
Look, I'm not criticising you
in any way whatsoever, Ms Pickering.

21:32.960 --> 21:34.840
I just think people
are taking on years of debt

21:34.920 --> 21:36.960
for a ceremony lasting
less than an hour.

21:37.080 --> 21:39.360
I've got to go, I'm afraid. You know...

21:39.640 --> 21:41.960
I thought I was helping
people celebrate

21:42.040 --> 21:44.880
a blessed sacrament,
but it seems I was wrong.

21:45.560 --> 21:48.120
It seems I've just been
driving people deeper

21:48.200 --> 21:50.120
and deeper into poverty and despair.

21:50.200 --> 21:52.560
-No, you aren't...
-I've got to go, I've got marking to do.

21:54.360 --> 21:55.360
[SIGHS]

22:07.440 --> 22:09.200
-[KNOCKING ON DOOR]
-That's Mariella.

22:10.120 --> 22:11.160
Mariella?

22:11.240 --> 22:12.800
-She's taking you out.
-LISA: I'll get it.

22:13.960 --> 22:16.080
[SCOFFS] Mum, I can't go
out looking like this.

22:16.160 --> 22:17.920
She's taking you out.

22:29.760 --> 22:30.760
[LAUGHING]

22:32.240 --> 22:35.040
-Have you tried Tom?
-Oh, yeah.

22:35.680 --> 22:36.680
And?

22:36.800 --> 22:40.160
-And he says he's skint.
-Do you believe him?

22:42.560 --> 22:43.560
You can't half pick 'em.

22:44.200 --> 22:46.000
-Thanks.
-You're welcome.

22:47.360 --> 22:50.080
So, there's this banana and a vibrator,
and they're in the top drawer,

22:50.280 --> 22:51.880
and the banana turns around and says,

22:51.960 --> 22:54.200
"Well, I don't know what you're shaking
for, she's going to eat me."

22:54.360 --> 22:55.880
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

22:56.200 --> 22:59.520
MAN: And then my missus, she's in front
of the mirror and she says,

22:59.760 --> 23:02.520
"I think I'd like me boobs
to be a bit bigger."

23:02.920 --> 23:05.840
I said, "Right, once or twice a day,
get a bit of tissue paper

23:05.920 --> 23:08.280
"and give 'em both a good wipe
with it."

23:08.760 --> 23:10.920
She says, "How's that
gonna make them bigger?"

23:11.200 --> 23:12.440
I said, "Well, it worked on
your ass, innit?"

23:13.080 --> 23:14.440
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

23:16.080 --> 23:18.880
MAN: Oh, here she comes.
What a beauty. Hello, love.

23:18.960 --> 23:21.040
-What a gorgeous outfit that is.
-Thanks very much.

23:21.120 --> 23:23.240
MAN: You're welcome.
Hey, you two must be sisters.

23:23.400 --> 23:25.040
What's the matter,
couldn't Cinderella make it?

23:25.680 --> 23:27.120
[MAN LAUGHING]

23:27.360 --> 23:29.760
Do you want one of these?
Do you want one of these?

23:30.040 --> 23:32.440
Oh, yeah, I thought it was a black eye.
I didn't notice that, love,

23:32.520 --> 23:34.320
I thought I was talking to a panda.

23:34.480 --> 23:36.000
You can't beat a good laugh.
It's gotta be

23:36.080 --> 23:37.760
the best medicine in the world, innit?

23:38.080 --> 23:42.000
Eh? Unless you're diabetic,
then insulin's fairly high on the list.

23:42.200 --> 23:44.880
Never thought I'd make meself
laugh with that one, that's dangerous.

23:45.000 --> 23:49.040
Oh, apart from one.
Hello, love, are you enjoying yourself?

23:49.560 --> 23:53.120
Well, tell your face that.
What are you drinking? Night nurse?

24:05.560 --> 24:08.720
♪ When your head is light
from too much wine

24:08.960 --> 24:13.240
♪ It's easy to cross the line

24:14.600 --> 24:18.360
♪ When the moon is bright
and the music's cool

24:18.640 --> 24:21.840
♪ It's easy to become a fool

24:22.720 --> 24:26.760
♪ I've made a list of things not to do

24:27.400 --> 24:29.440
♪ To stop me from loving you

24:33.280 --> 24:37.160
♪ Stay away from stars

24:37.720 --> 24:40.800
♪ Stop walking in the rain ♪

25:19.920 --> 25:20.920
[VOICES ECHOING]

25:30.160 --> 25:32.800
[WOMAN CRYING AND SCREAMING]

25:39.760 --> 25:40.920
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

25:41.000 --> 25:42.560
MAN 1: Watch it! You're getting kicked.

25:42.640 --> 25:44.120
-MAN 2: Go, John.
-[MEN CHEERING]

25:44.840 --> 25:46.400
Great goal, John.

25:47.640 --> 25:50.360
Skin that fat bastard, Allen! Skin him!

25:50.800 --> 25:53.000
Come on, lads! Get it over!

25:53.440 --> 25:54.680
Get it over, Eric.

25:55.960 --> 25:57.760
Pass it on to him!

25:57.840 --> 26:00.000
Right, come on, now!

26:00.360 --> 26:01.880
Come on. Go on!

26:02.720 --> 26:04.400
-[ALL CHEERING]
-[WHISTLE BLOWING]

26:04.480 --> 26:05.480
Yes!

26:05.640 --> 26:07.280
That's what you get
when you press, right?

26:07.520 --> 26:08.680
Good goal.

26:12.160 --> 26:13.560
There he is!

26:14.160 --> 26:15.160
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

26:16.120 --> 26:17.240
Hey, you, get on.

26:17.400 --> 26:19.240
Ref, ref, stop, ref!

26:19.440 --> 26:20.760
Can't stop a man who runs off.

26:20.880 --> 26:22.120
He's run off because we're shoving him!

26:22.840 --> 26:23.840
No chance.

26:24.040 --> 26:25.960
We told him he was coming off,
so he's run off.

26:26.360 --> 26:27.440
Would this man lie?

26:27.760 --> 26:28.840
Would this man lie?

26:29.120 --> 26:30.520
Would a man like this lie?

26:30.760 --> 26:32.400
-Ref! Ref!
-[BELL RINGS]

26:33.280 --> 26:34.320
Good morning.

26:34.440 --> 26:36.280
[CHILDREN SHOUTING INDISTINCTIVELY]

26:37.280 --> 26:38.720
If you wouldn't make
a bit of palaver and

26:38.800 --> 26:40.720
eat your burnt toast,
it wouldn't happen, would it?

26:40.800 --> 26:42.040
MICHAEL: Good morning,
good morning.

26:42.160 --> 26:43.440
CHRISTINA: Good morning. Hey, you.

26:43.840 --> 26:45.440
-In the wars again?
-What?

26:45.720 --> 26:46.800
Get your hand caught in the till?

26:47.240 --> 26:48.240
[CHUCKLES]

26:48.320 --> 26:49.400
It's a joke.

26:50.440 --> 26:51.440
Sorry.

26:51.640 --> 26:53.440
Mrs Evans, she's usually on gate.

26:53.560 --> 26:56.080
Oh, I'm standing in.
She won't be in until mid-morning.

26:57.160 --> 26:58.200
Why, is there a problem?

26:58.360 --> 26:59.600
He's got no dinner money

26:59.680 --> 27:01.640
and he's not going to have it
for the rest of the week, and...

27:02.040 --> 27:03.800
He's embarrassed about it, so...

27:03.920 --> 27:05.200
I said that I'd tell her.

27:05.280 --> 27:06.760
Oh, I could tell her if you want.

27:06.840 --> 27:08.920
-Would you?
-Yeah, no problem.

27:09.240 --> 27:11.320
-Did you hear that?
-Yeah.

27:11.400 --> 27:13.000
-And what do you say?
-Thank you, Father.

27:13.080 --> 27:14.120
Oh, you're welcome.

27:14.360 --> 27:15.360
Thank you.

27:15.560 --> 27:16.560
Anything else I can do?

27:17.200 --> 27:20.360
You could lend me 1,000 pounds?

27:20.480 --> 27:22.760
I'll pay you back ten quid a week
for the next 200 years.

27:25.080 --> 27:26.240
Can I come and see you sometime?

27:27.720 --> 27:29.360
Erm, why?

27:30.360 --> 27:31.720
Cos I think you're in pain.

27:33.800 --> 27:35.720
No. Real pain.

27:39.480 --> 27:41.280
I'm just skint, Father.

27:49.160 --> 27:50.160
[SIGHS]

27:52.920 --> 27:53.960
Can you look into this, please?

27:54.120 --> 27:55.120
It's company policy.

27:57.720 --> 27:59.200
We can only pay the melt-down price.

27:59.840 --> 28:00.880
Nine carat.

28:00.960 --> 28:01.960
Can't give them away.

28:04.080 --> 28:06.000
Common occurrence, is it,
women flogging their rings?

28:06.120 --> 28:07.120
Yeah.

28:07.280 --> 28:08.320
How much?

28:08.400 --> 28:09.400
30.

28:11.280 --> 28:13.120
No, I'm selling them, not pawning.

28:13.200 --> 28:14.760
It's the same thing.

28:15.760 --> 28:17.240
[SIGHS]

28:22.400 --> 28:23.400
Emerald?

28:23.840 --> 28:24.840
Yeah.

28:25.400 --> 28:26.480
Blame Frankie for that.

28:26.800 --> 28:28.200
-Sorry?
-Dettori.

28:28.480 --> 28:30.640
Came third in the 2005 derby.

28:30.840 --> 28:32.840
If he'd had come first,
I'd have got diamond.

28:33.240 --> 28:34.240
All right.

28:34.800 --> 28:35.920
All right, so how much?

28:36.320 --> 28:37.480
I can go to 70.

28:37.560 --> 28:39.800
70 and 30, that's 100 in total.

28:39.880 --> 28:41.080
No, 150.

28:41.280 --> 28:42.560
We don't bargain, I'm sorry.

28:43.000 --> 28:44.480
-100 and that's it.
-Right, well...

28:44.640 --> 28:48.520
Well, you can take your 100
and shove it up your hole.

29:00.520 --> 29:01.640
Shit.

29:12.360 --> 29:13.600
Oh.

29:14.000 --> 29:15.440
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

29:15.760 --> 29:16.760
Don't gloat.

29:17.000 --> 29:18.000
I won't.

29:21.280 --> 29:23.000
Oh, my God.
You knew I was coming back, didn't you?

29:23.080 --> 29:24.240
-Yeah.
-How?

29:24.600 --> 29:25.760
How did you know I'd come back?

29:25.840 --> 29:27.000
You didn't put the ring back on.

29:27.880 --> 29:30.160
The ones who tell me
to shove it up my hole

29:30.240 --> 29:31.680
as they're putting the ring back on,

29:31.760 --> 29:32.960
they don't come back.

29:33.160 --> 29:34.400
The others do.

29:35.560 --> 29:37.480
I've never had
a millionaire in here, love.

29:38.680 --> 29:42.440
If you're coming here,
you're skint and angry.

29:43.120 --> 29:45.560
But there's no politicians here,
so they give it to me.

29:45.920 --> 29:49.480
And I don't think that's fair, love,
because I'm skint, too.

29:50.520 --> 29:52.360
And though I'd like
to give everyone a break,

29:52.480 --> 29:56.080
I can't because I'll get sacked.

29:56.320 --> 30:00.080
And even though it's a shitty job
that gives me nothing but grief,

30:00.520 --> 30:02.800
it's still a job and I need it.

30:03.920 --> 30:04.920
Thank you.

30:07.360 --> 30:08.360
All right.

30:16.800 --> 30:17.800
Thanks.

30:24.240 --> 30:25.520
Just a minute, all right?

30:41.280 --> 30:42.880
-[DOOR OPENS]
-CHRISTINA: Hi, Mum.

30:45.480 --> 30:46.520
[CHRISTINA SIGHS]

30:48.000 --> 30:49.080
Mum?

30:50.160 --> 30:51.200
Mum!

31:03.760 --> 31:04.800
Mum?

31:15.680 --> 31:16.760
Mum.

31:24.120 --> 31:25.120
Mum...

31:27.840 --> 31:28.840
Mum.

31:31.200 --> 31:32.200
Mum.

31:34.520 --> 31:36.280
Oh, no, Mum.

31:39.520 --> 31:40.640
Mum?

31:59.720 --> 32:00.720
No.

32:03.120 --> 32:04.120
Oh...

32:15.360 --> 32:16.720
[SOBBING] Oh, no.

32:17.360 --> 32:18.360
[PHONE BEEPS]

32:27.600 --> 32:29.120
Are you still getting the flashbacks?

32:29.680 --> 32:30.680
Yeah.

32:34.280 --> 32:35.400
Are they just as frequent?

32:37.280 --> 32:38.280
More.

32:39.200 --> 32:41.240
I've done one or two decent things
in my life, Peter,

32:41.320 --> 32:43.760
I really have,
but I never flash back to them.

32:44.080 --> 32:45.240
[MOBILE RINGING]

32:46.000 --> 32:47.040
It's on answer.

32:47.600 --> 32:49.040
[MOBILE RINGING]

32:49.760 --> 32:51.680
MICHAEL:
You've reached father Michael Kerrigan.

32:51.760 --> 32:53.480
I can't get to the phone at the moment.

32:53.560 --> 32:55.600
If you'd like to leave a message
and your phone number,

32:55.720 --> 32:57.440
I'll get back to you
as soon as possible.

32:58.160 --> 32:59.160
Thanks.

33:00.880 --> 33:02.000
Help.

33:06.840 --> 33:07.840
[PHONE BEEPS]

33:08.320 --> 33:09.320
I hate that.

33:10.640 --> 33:12.800
A sane priest would assume
it wasn't important,

33:12.880 --> 33:15.400
otherwise, they'd have left a message,
but I can't do that.

33:15.680 --> 33:18.560
I assume they didn't leave a message
because it was too important,

33:18.680 --> 33:22.320
too heart-breaking, too gut-wrenching
to speak to a bloody answering machine.

33:22.400 --> 33:23.400
[PHONE BEEPS]

33:23.480 --> 33:26.200
I'm a shitty priest, I am,
to expect them to do so.

33:27.360 --> 33:29.200
[CLEARS THROAT]

33:30.600 --> 33:32.320
[PHONE RINGING]

33:38.520 --> 33:39.520
[PHONE BEEPS]

33:40.880 --> 33:41.960
Hello?

33:42.640 --> 33:45.120
MICHAEL: [ON PHONE] Hi, there.
It's father Michael Kerrigan here.

33:45.200 --> 33:47.320
You rang me just now.

33:49.600 --> 33:51.640
Yeah, Father.
I dialled the wrong number.

33:54.400 --> 33:55.400
[PHONE BEEPS]

33:57.120 --> 33:58.200
[SIGHS]

34:19.760 --> 34:20.920
[SOBBING]

34:47.240 --> 34:48.320
[SNIFFLES]

35:57.400 --> 35:59.640
[SOBBING]

36:05.160 --> 36:07.720
Yeah, I thought that Nan
was picking them up,

36:07.800 --> 36:09.360
and she thought
that I was picking them up.

36:09.560 --> 36:11.320
So, I'll be there
in two minutes, all right?

36:40.120 --> 36:43.360
Come here. I want hugs.

36:43.640 --> 36:45.520
I want big hugs.

36:46.480 --> 36:47.480
[EXCLAIMS]

36:54.080 --> 36:55.240
[SNIFFLES]

36:55.320 --> 36:56.320
Hey.

36:56.400 --> 36:58.200
-What's up?
-Nothing.

36:58.480 --> 36:59.600
Why're you crying?

37:00.760 --> 37:02.200
I'm not. I just...

37:03.160 --> 37:04.480
I just want big hugs.

37:18.040 --> 37:19.120
MICHAEL: Hello, Jean.

37:22.320 --> 37:23.360
I had a fight.

37:23.440 --> 37:24.520
Anyone I know?

37:25.360 --> 37:26.880
Yeah.

37:27.280 --> 37:28.600
Rosie Lunt's daughter.

37:30.000 --> 37:31.000
Right.

37:31.080 --> 37:33.520
I told Steven it was over work,
but it weren't really.

37:34.960 --> 37:35.960
I, erm...

37:37.040 --> 37:39.400
I found out that it's my fault
that we can't have kids.

37:40.360 --> 37:42.520
I think he always knew
but just didn't say anything.

37:42.800 --> 37:44.200
It shows how good of a man he is.

37:45.200 --> 37:46.480
How good a father he'd have been.

37:46.840 --> 37:48.240
It just makes it all the more...

37:49.600 --> 37:50.600
Painful.

37:54.720 --> 37:56.440
Shall I let you into a secret?

37:57.320 --> 37:58.320
Yeah.

38:00.240 --> 38:02.520
I'm not the Virgin Mary's biggest fan.

38:03.840 --> 38:05.200
-No?
-No.

38:06.800 --> 38:10.640
I think, a few hundred years ago,
a cardinal went to see the Pope

38:10.720 --> 38:14.360
and he said, "Have you seen what
this guy Christ actually said?"

38:14.880 --> 38:16.960
And the Pope walks up to him and goes,

38:17.040 --> 38:19.280
"Don't start talking about his mother.
She said nothing."

38:19.400 --> 38:20.720
[CHUCKLES]

38:22.720 --> 38:24.480
She did find it easy, though,
didn't she?

38:25.440 --> 38:27.360
Ridiculously easy to get pregnant.

38:28.320 --> 38:31.480
So, I think this is her department,
don't you?

38:31.920 --> 38:32.920
Yeah.

38:35.680 --> 38:36.800
Shall we pray to her?

38:37.160 --> 38:38.520
Yeah, please.

38:39.360 --> 38:42.080
BOTH: Hail Mary, full of grace,
the Lord is with thee.

38:42.640 --> 38:44.520
Blessed art thou amongst women,

38:44.600 --> 38:47.440
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

38:48.120 --> 38:49.960
Holy Mary, mother of God,

38:50.520 --> 38:53.920
pray for us sinners,
now and at the hour of our death.

38:54.320 --> 38:55.320
Amen.

38:59.240 --> 39:01.640
Right, now, listen.

39:02.320 --> 39:04.680
I need to tell you something
very important.

39:05.280 --> 39:08.200
Your nana's ill and she's in bed,

39:08.680 --> 39:11.240
and you're not to go up to her
until I say so, all right?

39:11.920 --> 39:12.920
Promise me.

39:13.000 --> 39:14.160
ALL: Okay, okay.

39:14.240 --> 39:15.320
She needs peace.

39:16.720 --> 39:18.560
-Right?
-LISA: Right.

39:52.840 --> 39:53.840
No.

40:23.400 --> 40:24.600
[SCREECHES]

40:43.040 --> 40:44.480
What? I just told you that, didn't I?

40:44.560 --> 40:45.920
I don't know how much
is going to go in there.

40:46.000 --> 40:47.040
It could be half a month's wages.

40:47.120 --> 40:48.800
I could be nothing. Put that down.

40:48.880 --> 40:49.880
Can you get off that?

40:49.960 --> 40:50.960
No, but whatever it is,

40:51.040 --> 40:53.200
it's not going to be enough
to cover the direct debit

40:53.280 --> 40:54.720
and then you're going to charge me
for it, aren't you?

40:54.800 --> 40:56.320
-And I don't want you to do that.
-They're wet.

40:56.400 --> 40:57.680
Yeah? Well, hopefully, in the future

40:57.760 --> 40:59.040
you'll remember
to take them out of the bag

40:59.120 --> 41:00.480
and put them in the dirty washing,
won't you?

41:00.760 --> 41:01.920
Sorry, I'm trying to get them...

41:02.000 --> 41:03.200
-They're wet.
-The kids ready for school.

41:03.280 --> 41:04.640
Erm, yes, I know they're wet.

41:04.720 --> 41:06.080
JIMMY: I can't go to school
with these shorts wet.

41:06.160 --> 41:07.560
CHRISTINA: Excuse me. Sorry, I'm...

41:07.640 --> 41:09.400
You're just gonna have to wear them wet,
aren't you?

41:09.480 --> 41:10.480
JIMMY: I can't wear them wet.

41:10.560 --> 41:12.840
Sorry, I'll have to call you back.

41:12.920 --> 41:14.160
-JIMMY: Mum!
-What are you doing?

41:14.840 --> 41:15.840
Get down here.

41:17.840 --> 41:18.880
What do you think you're doing?

41:19.320 --> 41:20.920
Taking Grandma a cup of tea.

41:21.560 --> 41:23.080
But I told you not to go in there,
didn't I?

41:23.960 --> 41:26.280
Her head's banging
and she needs peace and quiet.

41:26.360 --> 41:28.200
Absolute peace and quiet.

41:28.800 --> 41:29.800
Right.

41:30.840 --> 41:31.840
Hey.

41:34.280 --> 41:36.120
Okay, it's not your fault.
Go on, go in there.

41:43.560 --> 41:45.160
CHRISTINA: Thirteen weeks
till I can claim?

41:45.240 --> 41:46.480
-Yes.
-Sorry. I'm...

41:46.560 --> 41:47.800
Well, you said I might be able
to get a loan.

41:48.400 --> 41:49.720
Well, it's unlikely, I'm afraid.

41:49.960 --> 41:51.480
-So, if you just...
-All right, so what do I do?

41:51.560 --> 41:52.920
We'll find you a job,
if you just take...

41:53.000 --> 41:55.720
I'm a betting shop manager
who stole from her employer.

41:55.800 --> 41:57.680
What kind of chance does that give me?

41:57.760 --> 41:59.000
Well, there are other jobs.

41:59.520 --> 42:01.360
Oh, yeah, I sold 'em.

42:01.440 --> 42:03.280
You clocked 'em last time.
I sold 'em. I got 100 quid.

42:03.360 --> 42:05.080
And I didn't piss it up a wall
or go down the bingo.

42:05.280 --> 42:06.400
I filled the fridge with it.

42:07.760 --> 42:08.840
What do I do?

42:09.240 --> 42:11.480
Well, maybe there are other things
that you could sell.

43:04.920 --> 43:05.960
Hiya. You all right?

43:06.280 --> 43:07.280
Hi, Father.

43:07.520 --> 43:09.120
-Is your mum in?
-Yeah.

43:10.640 --> 43:12.040
-Can I see her?
-She's sick.

43:13.240 --> 43:14.880
-I know.
-You know?

43:15.240 --> 43:16.320
Yeah, she phoned me.

43:16.440 --> 43:17.680
She said she couldn't make the meeting

43:17.760 --> 43:19.200
so I thought I'd bring it all 'round.

43:19.320 --> 43:21.800
Em, yeah, well, I'll give it to her.

43:21.920 --> 43:23.560
There's stuff I said we'd talk about.

43:23.640 --> 43:25.800
No, she's, she's... Too sick for that.

43:26.520 --> 43:27.640
I'm her priest.

43:27.960 --> 43:29.400
I'm used to seeing sick people,

43:29.560 --> 43:30.560
dead ones, even.

43:31.280 --> 43:32.280
[CHUCKLES]

43:32.880 --> 43:33.960
[CHUCKLES] Sorry.

43:34.040 --> 43:35.920
All right.
Well, then, I'll tell her you called.

43:36.000 --> 43:37.040
Well...

43:37.960 --> 43:39.040
I brought you these.

43:40.760 --> 43:41.760
What are they?

43:42.080 --> 43:45.000
Eh, they're vouchers for the food bank.

43:45.840 --> 43:47.520
We all need a bit of help now and again.

43:48.200 --> 43:50.000
Will you... Will you go, Father?

43:50.080 --> 43:51.720
It's not what you imagine, Christina...

43:51.800 --> 43:53.920
-Please. Father, will you...
-They judge no one...

43:54.120 --> 43:55.120
Will you just go?

43:56.880 --> 43:57.880
Okay.

43:58.840 --> 43:59.840
If you change your mind...

44:00.720 --> 44:01.720
I won't change my mind.

44:02.920 --> 44:05.600
-You tell your mum I called in, yeah?
-Yeah.

44:06.240 --> 44:08.120
She'll be really pleased you called.
Thanks.

44:08.240 --> 44:09.360
Sorry I've upset you.

44:11.320 --> 44:12.360
All right.

44:19.800 --> 44:21.040
-[VACUUM CLEANER WHIRRING]
-[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

44:22.320 --> 44:23.480
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

44:28.080 --> 44:29.960
Didn't know you'd be home.
I didn't get you a cake.

44:35.160 --> 44:36.160
Where's Mum?

44:36.240 --> 44:37.240
Out!

44:37.320 --> 44:38.320
Where?

44:39.080 --> 44:40.160
I don't know, she said...

44:40.280 --> 44:41.360
It's Wednesday.

44:41.520 --> 44:42.880
I always come around on a Wednesday.

44:43.560 --> 44:45.480
Well, you know what she's like.

44:46.040 --> 44:47.440
All right, you can have her cake.

44:50.240 --> 44:52.480
[SPRAYING]

44:53.840 --> 44:55.320
Did she go to the doctor's?

44:56.960 --> 44:57.960
What?

44:58.600 --> 45:00.280
[SHOUTING] Did she go to the doctor's?

45:02.520 --> 45:04.080
Erm...

45:04.600 --> 45:05.600
No.

45:05.880 --> 45:07.000
She said she'd go this morning.

45:07.880 --> 45:08.880
Why?

45:09.200 --> 45:10.200
She's getting chest pains.

45:11.920 --> 45:12.920
Why didn't you tell me?

45:13.080 --> 45:14.800
You live under the same roof as her.
I thought you'd know.

45:14.880 --> 45:16.160
Well, I didn't... I don't.

45:16.800 --> 45:17.800
Can I go for the kids?

45:18.200 --> 45:19.200
No.

45:19.280 --> 45:21.120
Well, we usually pick them up,
me and Mum.

45:21.880 --> 45:23.040
Yeah, well, erm...

45:23.800 --> 45:26.240
I've got to be there
or Mum's got to be there, so...

45:26.400 --> 45:28.600
All right, I'll go with you, then.
Is that a problem?

45:29.280 --> 45:30.320
No.

45:30.400 --> 45:31.920
They like it when I go for them.

45:32.280 --> 45:33.280
Great.

45:34.960 --> 45:35.960
Summat wrong?

45:36.360 --> 45:37.360
No, not at all.

45:39.720 --> 45:40.720
[SIGHS]

45:43.400 --> 45:44.400
[CHUCKLES]

45:45.200 --> 45:46.360
Come here, Trouble.

45:46.640 --> 45:48.360
[GRUNTS] Gosh.

45:50.640 --> 45:52.080
-Who's this for?
-Grandma.

45:52.880 --> 45:53.880
She's been sick?

45:54.080 --> 45:55.080
Erm...

45:55.640 --> 45:57.240
[STAMMERS] A couple of days,
but she's all right now.

45:57.320 --> 45:58.520
-What was it?
-Yeah?

45:58.720 --> 46:00.600
Erm, just a bit of a cold.

46:00.680 --> 46:01.680
We can't go in her room.

46:01.800 --> 46:03.640
-What, she went to bed with it?
-Yeah.

46:03.720 --> 46:04.880
A bit of a cold?

46:05.560 --> 46:07.080
Yes, but she's all right now.

46:07.720 --> 46:09.680
Yeah, all right.

46:33.800 --> 46:35.200
All right. In you get.

46:36.880 --> 46:37.880
Go on.

46:39.920 --> 46:40.920
My coat.

46:48.960 --> 46:50.560
Hey! Hey, where you going?

46:50.760 --> 46:52.480
Wait, shh, what are you doing?

46:52.560 --> 46:53.800
I'm taking this up to Nan.

46:58.440 --> 46:59.720
Come on, I'll give it to her.

47:00.200 --> 47:01.200
Go in there.

47:02.640 --> 47:03.800
Mum's back?

47:05.120 --> 47:06.120
Yeah.

47:06.840 --> 47:08.080
What? She took the small one.

47:09.120 --> 47:10.200
Mum's purse.

47:10.760 --> 47:11.760
Where is she?

47:15.720 --> 47:16.720
Upstairs.

47:20.120 --> 47:21.320
All right, kids, we're, erm...

47:21.400 --> 47:22.480
We're going to go and see Nan.

47:22.560 --> 47:23.560
Can you guys stay here?

47:25.000 --> 47:26.000
Stay here.

47:30.720 --> 47:32.240
Hey, hey, hey!

47:32.400 --> 47:33.520
Hey! She's dead.

47:56.880 --> 47:57.880
Mum.

48:03.080 --> 48:04.200
[SNIFFLES]

48:16.000 --> 48:17.400
I just... I found her like that.

48:17.520 --> 48:18.720
Well, not like that, but...

48:19.720 --> 48:21.240
-Dead.
-[SOBS]

48:25.160 --> 48:26.440
Did you get her a priest?

48:29.640 --> 48:30.640
No.

48:30.760 --> 48:33.200
Well, I guess she'd want a priest.

48:33.800 --> 48:36.160
[SNIFFLES] You know what all that
meant to her.

48:37.960 --> 48:39.720
You guys know that.

48:46.880 --> 48:47.880
We can't call him yet.

48:48.160 --> 48:49.400
Well, why not?

48:52.880 --> 48:54.600
Because she gets her pension tomorrow.

48:57.800 --> 48:58.800
What?

49:00.040 --> 49:01.320
I'm skint, no...

49:02.560 --> 49:04.240
No job, no dole, no nothing, erm...

49:06.720 --> 49:07.720
I need her pension.

49:08.440 --> 49:09.440
Oh, my God, you can't...

49:09.600 --> 49:10.760
I've got three kids to feed.

49:10.880 --> 49:13.000
That's why you lied to me
and said she was out.

49:14.000 --> 49:15.000
Yeah.

49:15.960 --> 49:17.880
You weren't even going to tell me.

49:19.760 --> 49:20.960
Oh, my God.

49:22.440 --> 49:24.640
Please. I don't want the kids to hear.

49:28.240 --> 49:29.280
When did this happen?

49:30.040 --> 49:31.600
-How long has she been like this?
-Mariella, please.

49:31.680 --> 49:33.560
I don't want the kids to hear.

49:33.720 --> 49:34.720
Three days.

49:41.280 --> 49:42.640
You heartless,

49:44.320 --> 49:45.720
scheming bitch.

49:46.880 --> 49:47.880
I'm sorry.

49:49.520 --> 49:51.520
Can you leave me with her, please?

49:53.080 --> 49:54.800
Can you leave me alone with my mother?

49:55.520 --> 49:56.520
Please.

49:58.800 --> 49:59.800
I'm sorry.

50:07.280 --> 50:08.280
[DOOR SHUTS]

50:29.840 --> 50:30.840
I'm sorry.

50:32.080 --> 50:33.160
You took her ring.

50:33.880 --> 50:34.880
Yeah, but...

50:35.480 --> 50:36.600
I didn't sell it.

50:38.240 --> 50:40.080
Look, I didn't sell it.
I couldn't sell it.

50:41.880 --> 50:43.120
Look, look here.

50:47.560 --> 50:49.280
Please don't say anything, will you?
Please?

50:49.400 --> 50:50.760
Will you? Please don't...

51:07.040 --> 51:08.720
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

51:26.200 --> 51:27.200
Who's that for?

51:30.160 --> 51:31.160
My mum.

51:55.600 --> 51:57.200
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

52:06.840 --> 52:09.240
Erm, yeah, I've come
to get my mum's pension.

52:09.320 --> 52:11.040
All right, stick the card
in the machine, then.

52:11.520 --> 52:12.720
It'll just ask you for its PIN.

52:15.960 --> 52:16.960
How is she?

52:18.320 --> 52:19.640
Yeah, she's not too good.

52:20.040 --> 52:21.040
Is it her chest?

52:21.160 --> 52:22.160
What?

52:22.800 --> 52:24.160
She said last time...

52:25.560 --> 52:26.680
Oh, erm...

52:26.960 --> 52:28.000
[CARD MACHINE BEEPS]

52:28.160 --> 52:29.160
Yeah.

52:32.840 --> 52:34.000
Yeah, she's doing all right now.

52:34.880 --> 52:35.880
Tell her I was asking.

52:36.320 --> 52:37.320
Oh, I will.

52:40.560 --> 52:41.760
-Thanks.
-Bye.

52:55.960 --> 52:57.640
[PHONE BEEPS]

53:05.880 --> 53:08.160
MICHAEL: [ON PHONE] Hi,
it's Father Michael Kerrigan here.

53:08.240 --> 53:10.520
It's Christina Fitzsimmons,
Rosie's daughter.

53:12.400 --> 53:13.400
She's...

53:14.000 --> 53:15.560
Died suddenly, Father.

53:15.880 --> 53:17.800
MICHAEL: Christina, I'm so sorry.

53:23.160 --> 53:24.240
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

53:27.600 --> 53:29.200
I'm so sorry, Christina.

53:35.200 --> 53:36.640
Thank you, Father.

54:03.080 --> 54:04.200
I'll miss you, Rosie.

54:10.000 --> 54:11.000
When did she die?

54:11.720 --> 54:14.160
Between 10 o'clock last night
and 10 o'clock this morning, Father,

54:14.240 --> 54:15.680
when I found her.

54:17.440 --> 54:18.680
Would you mind if I light a candle?

54:20.440 --> 54:21.480
No.

54:22.880 --> 54:24.960
It's easy to forget that Christ is here,

54:25.320 --> 54:27.320
giving us strength, easing our pain.

54:29.120 --> 54:30.720
The candle reminds us of that fact.

54:35.400 --> 54:37.320
She's been dead a few days, Christina.

54:37.600 --> 54:38.680
That's not possible, Father.

54:39.960 --> 54:41.440
I'm sorry, Christina, but...

54:42.640 --> 54:43.920
Was it her pension?

54:45.040 --> 54:46.200
I don't know what
you're talking about, Father.

54:46.280 --> 54:48.520
Christina, we'll need a doctor
to certify death.

54:48.600 --> 54:50.160
He'll know she's been dead for days.

54:50.240 --> 54:51.320
He'll call the police.

54:51.400 --> 54:53.840
The first thing they'll do is check
when her pension was last drawn.

54:54.080 --> 54:55.440
When was that?

54:56.600 --> 54:58.080
Did you know
that she was having chest pains?

54:58.160 --> 54:59.160
Yeah.

54:59.240 --> 55:00.320
Did you know she was having chest pains?

55:00.400 --> 55:01.400
-Yes...
-Because I didn't.

55:01.480 --> 55:02.480
Everyone else knew, but I didn't know.

55:02.560 --> 55:04.000
When was her pension
last drawn, Christina?

55:08.240 --> 55:10.960
-An hour ago.
-Oh, Christina.

55:11.040 --> 55:13.400
-[SOBBING]
-Come here.

55:13.520 --> 55:15.560
Am I going to go to prison, Father?

55:17.400 --> 55:18.520
I don't know.

55:18.640 --> 55:20.160
[CHRISTINA SOBBING]

55:20.240 --> 55:21.240
It's all right.

55:24.520 --> 55:26.840
-Will you join me in a prayer?
-[SOBBING]

55:28.080 --> 55:29.120
[SNIFFLES]

55:29.200 --> 55:30.240
[SOBBING]

55:33.680 --> 55:35.200
I miss her.

55:36.760 --> 55:38.680
BOTH: Our Father,
who art in heaven,

55:38.880 --> 55:40.160
hallowed be thy name,

55:40.360 --> 55:41.640
Thy kingdom come,

55:41.880 --> 55:42.880
Thy will be done,

55:43.160 --> 55:44.920
on Earth, as it is in heaven.

55:45.600 --> 55:47.120
Give us this day our daily bread,

55:47.200 --> 55:48.640
and forgive us our trespasses,

55:49.160 --> 55:51.960
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

55:52.520 --> 55:54.840
And lead us not into temptation,

55:55.000 --> 55:56.760
but deliver us from evil.

55:57.440 --> 55:58.560
Amen.

56:00.040 --> 56:01.560
[CHRISTINA SNIFFLES]

56:08.440 --> 56:09.440
What now?

56:11.200 --> 56:15.560
♪ Tell me what it's like in heaven

56:15.880 --> 56:19.200
♪ I hope it's kinder
than it is down here

56:20.560 --> 56:24.920
♪ With all the trials and tribulations

56:25.160 --> 56:28.320
♪ All the worry and living in fear

56:29.840 --> 56:32.320
♪ Hallelujah

56:32.440 --> 56:35.400
♪ Hallelujah

56:35.480 --> 56:37.320
♪ We might be bruised

56:37.480 --> 56:40.360
♪ But we're not broken
